# Local docker-compose environment.
#
# Copy this to `.env` at the repo root (alongside `package.json`). The
# `docker compose` invocation in scripts/dev-*.sh runs from this directory,
# so the file is picked up automatically.
#
# Nothing here is required — every variable has a sensible default — but
# the entries below are the ones most people change.

# ---- Codebase to index ----------------------------------------------------
#
# Mounted read-only into the worker AND the file-watcher sidecar at
# /workspace. The `code_indexer` pipeline (and the bundled
# codebase-ingest-* demos) walk this path; the file-watcher sidecar
# subscribes to changes on it. Default: the RAGdoll repo itself, so the
# smoke pipeline works on a fresh checkout.
#
# CODEBASE_PATH=/Users/you/IdeaProjects/your-codebase

# ---- File-watcher sidecar -------------------------------------------------
#
# When set, the sidecar POSTs to this URL on every debounced change burst,
# so the pipeline re-runs incrementally. Create a webhook trigger for your
# pipeline (`POST /api/pipelines/<id>/triggers`) and paste its
# `webhookUrl` here.
#
# Unset = sidecar starts but skips POSTs (and logs a warning) — fine for
# manual / cron-driven runs.
#
# FILE_WATCHER_WEBHOOK_URL=http://api:3001/api/triggers/webhook/<token>
# FILE_WATCHER_DEBOUNCE_MS=5000
# FILE_WATCHER_IGNORE=node_modules,.git,dist,build,.next,.cache
